            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Zest your <strong>lime[s]</strong> (try to grate lightly and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter) and cut in half</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>sliced onion </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) to a small bowl and squeeze the<strong> </strong>juice<strong> </strong>of <strong>half </strong>your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lime[s] </strong>over, then place the <strong>squeezed half[ves]</strong> on top for added pickling – this is your <strong>zingy quick-pickled onion</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1623677955619-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
